              <li>Reframed package offerings from post-selection upsells into an early-stage discovery layer by enabling item-to-package mapping before provider selection, increasing bundle visibility and conversion potential.</li>
              <li>Leveraged behavioral data and provider feedback to identify friction and decision breakdowns across booking and provider workflows, guiding prioritized UX improvements.</li>
              <li>Used HTML/CSS/JS and AI-assisted prototyping to simulate production-like flows and accelerate iteration with engineering.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="spacingSmall"></div>
          <div class="element">
            <h4><strong>BookYourPet | UX Designer </strong></h4>
            <h6 class="textItalic">Oct 2021 – Oct 2024, Full-Time</h6>
            <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>

            <ul class="disc">
              <li>Solo UX designer for an end-to-end B2B subscription platform, partnering closely with the CTO and CEO to define service setup, scheduling, and booking systems for pet-care businesses.</li>
              <li>Identified and addressed rigid, tightly coupled system behaviors by working across feature dependencies, helping shift the platform toward a more flexible and scalable service configuration model.</li>
              <li>Designed a configurable booking system supporting multiple business types and hybrids (grooming, walking, training), enabling complex services and pricing within a unified calendar and booking structure.</li>
              <li>Built and maintained a Figma-based design system to support consistent booking experiences across provider setup and consumer flows.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="spacingXSmall"></div>
          </div>
